{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_vrtx_01MMsR2sYJiWpg2m7Jypd43P","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have everything I need. Here's the complete implementation:\n\n---\n\n## Implementation\n\n### 1. New file: `config/monitoring/prometheus-alert-rules.yaml`\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: monitoring.coreos.com/v1\nkind: PrometheusRule\nmetadata:\n  labels:\n    app.kubernetes.io/name: prometheusrule\n    app.kubernetes.io/instance: multiarch-tuning-operator\n    app.kubernetes.io/component: monitoring\n    app.kubernetes.io/part-of: multiarch-tuning-operator\n    app.kubernetes.io/managed-by: kustomize\n  name: image-inspection-alerts\n  namespace: system\nspec:\n  groups:\n    - name: multiarch-tuning-operator.rules\n      rules:\n        - alert: MultiarchImageInspectionFailureRateCritical\n          expr: |\n            (\n              rate(mto_ppo_ctrl_failed_image_inspection_total[5m])\n              /\n              clamp_min(rate(mto_ppo_ctrl_processed_pods_total[5m]), 1)\n            ) > 0.05\n          for: 10m\n          labels:\n            severity: critical\n          annotations:\n            summary: \"Multiarch Tuning Operator image inspection failure rate is critically high\"\n            message: >-\n              The image inspection failure rate has exceeded 5% over the last 5 minutes\n              for more than 10 minutes. This may indicate issues with registry\n              connectivity, image pull credentials, or malformed image references.\n              Current failure rate is {{ $value | humanizePercentage }}.\n```\n\n**Rationale for the PromQL expression:**\n- `mto_ppo_ctrl_failed_image_inspection_total` — counter of failed image inspections (defined in `internal/controller/podplacement/metrics/controller.go:66`, incremented in `internal/controller/podplacement/pod_model.go:502`)\n- `mto_ppo_ctrl_processed_pods_total` — counter of total processed pods (defined in `internal/controller/podplacement/metrics/controller.go:60`, incremented in `internal/controller/podplacement/pod_reconciler.go:88`)\n- `rate(...[5m])` computes the per-second rate over a 5-minute window\n- `clamp_min(..., 1)` prevents division by zero when no pods are being processed\n- `> 0.05` fires at a 5% failure rate threshold (the SLO)\n- `for: 10m` requires the condition to hold for 10 minutes before firing, preventing transient spikes from paging\n\n### 2. New file: `config/monitoring/kustomization.yaml`\n\n```yaml\nresources:\n  - prometheus-alert-rules.yaml\n```\n\n### 3. No other files require changes\n\nThe `config/monitoring/` directory is new and self-contained. To wire it into the operator's deployment, uncomment or add `- ../monitoring` in `config/default/kustomization.yaml` under `resources:`. However, the task asks only for the monitoring resource itself. If you want to include it in the default kustomize overlay, add this line to `config/default/kustomization.yaml`:\n\n```yaml\nresources:\n- ../crd\n- ../rbac\n- ../manager\n- ../webhook\n- ../monitoring   # <-- add this line\n```\n\n### Commands to validate\n\n```bash\n# Create the monitoring directory\nmkdir -p config/monitoring\n\n# (After writing both files above)\n\n# Validate the YAML is well-formed\nkubectl apply --dry-run=client -f config/monitoring/prometheus-alert-rules.yaml\n\n# Build the kustomize overlay to verify it resolves\nkustomize build config/monitoring\n```"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":562,"cache_read_input_tokens":39938,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":562,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ee2b5e0d-cb22-4ebe-8d76-1f40028a55d7","uuid":"e541e4a0-7fbe-4b0d-b615-f0091b7d33f5","timestamp":"2026-07-16T14:06:37.107Z","request_id":"req_vrtx_011Cd5s8uLg8oGyp1aCr8LnK"}
